"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/12/09/multimedia/09Syria-timeline-add-02-ftlj/09Syria-timeline-add-02-ftlj-articleLarge.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 600w,https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/12/09/multimedia/09Syria-timeline-add-02-ftlj/09Syria-timeline-add-02-ftlj-jumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1024w,https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/12/09/multimedia/09Syria-timeline-add-02-ftlj/09Syria-timeline-add-02-ftlj-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 2048w\" sizes=\"100vw\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"link-3c06c6f6\" data-testid=\"headline\"\u003e12 Days That Changed Syria: The Rebel Offensive in Visuals\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cfigcaption data-testid=\"photoviewer-children-ImageCaption\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCredit...\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan aria-hidden=\"false\"\u003eDaniel Berehulak/The New York Times\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"link-3c06c6f6\" data-testid=\"headline\"\u003e12 Days That Changed Syria: The Rebel Offensive in Visuals\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/header\u003e\u003cp aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCredit...\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003eDaniel Berehulak/The New York Times\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ctime datetime=\"2024-12-10T00:01:37-05:00\"\u003eDec. 10, 2024\u003c/time\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003csection name=\"articleBody\"\u003e\u003cdiv data-testid=\"companionColumn-0\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eIn just two weeks, rebel forces tore across Syria, shattering the stalemate left by more than a decade of civil war and bringing an end to more than five decades of brutal rule by the Assad dynasty.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe pace of the advance was as dizzying as its implications.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eHere’s how it unfolded in photos, videos and maps:\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eNOV. 27\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"link-41b63596\"\u003eThe offensive begins\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv data-testid=\"companionColumn-1\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe first thrust was sudden.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eFor years, the Islamist group Hayat Tahrir al-Sham consolidated control in its stronghold in Idlib in Syria’s northwest. Then on Nov. 27, the rebels suddenly began a rapid push east toward Aleppo, a major city that suffered some of the most brutal and protracted fighting during the country’s long civil war.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv data-testid=\"ImageBlock-3\"\u003e\u003cfigure aria-label=\"media\" role=\"group\"\u003e\u003cdiv data-testid=\"photoviewer-children-figure\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eImage\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 599px) and (min-device-pixel-ratio: 3),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 3dppx),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 288dpi)\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/12/09/multimedia/09syria-timeline-01-kzgq/09syria-timeline-01-kzgq-mobileMasterAt3x.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\u0026amp;disable=upscale\u0026amp;width=1800\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 599px) and (min-device-pixel-ratio: 2),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 2dppx),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 192dpi)\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/12/09/multimedia/09syria-timeline-01-kzgq/09syria-timeline-01-kzgq-mobileMasterAt3x.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\u0026amp;disable=upscale\u0026amp;width=1200\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 599px) and (min-device-pixel-ratio: 1),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 1dppx),(max-width: 599px) and (min-resolution: 96dpi)\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/12/09/multimedia/09syria-timeline-01-kzgq/09syria-timeline-01-kzgq-mobileMasterAt3x.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\u0026amp;disable=upscale\u0026amp;width=600\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Fighters in the dark against a rock wall, wearing balaclavas with reflective head bands.\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/12/09/multimedia/09syria-timeline-01-kzgq/09syria-timeline-01-kzgq-articleLarge.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\u0026amp;disable=upscale\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/12/09/multimedia/09syria-timeline-01-kzgq/09syria-timeline-01-kzgq-articleLarge.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 600w,https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/12/09/multimedia/09syria-timeline-01-kzgq/09syria-timeline-01-kzgq-jumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1024w,https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/12/09/multimedia/09syria-timeline-01-kzgq/09syria-timeline-01-kzgq-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 2048w\" sizes=\"((min-width: 600px) and (max-width: 1004px)) 84vw, (min-width: 1005px) 80vw, 100vw\" uri=\"nyt://image/dda5a3b2-ce55-5cfa-b851-3093749df418\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cfigcaption data-testid=\"photoviewer-children-caption\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eRebel fighters outside Atarib, western Aleppo Province, Nov. 27.\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCredit...\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan aria-hidden=\"false\"\u003eAbdulaziz Ketaz/Agence France-Presse — Getty Images\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv data-testid=\"companionColumn-2\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eOn Nov. 27, the rebels announced a striking initial success: They had overrun a Syrian government base, captured soldiers, taken tanks and seized several villages. “In a matter of about 10 hours,” \u003ca href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2024/11/27/world/middleeast/syria-opposition-forces-bases.html\" title=\"\"\u003ean analyst told The Times that day\u003c/a\u003e, the rebels were within a few miles of Aleppo.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv data-testid=\"VideoBlock-5\"\u003e\u003cfigure aria-label=\"media\" role=\"group\" data-testid=\"VideoBlock\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eVideo\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/12/09/09vid-Syria-Stack-30715-cover/09vid-Syria-Stack-30715-cover-threeByTwoLargeAt2X.jpg\" alt=\"Video player loading\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\u003cspan data-testid=\"video-summary\"\u003eRebel fighters drove through Al-Talhiya, Syria, as they advanced toward Aleppo on Nov. 29.\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCredit\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCredit...\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003eAssociated Press\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv data-testid=\"Optimistic-10\"\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"optimistic-truncator-a11y\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\u003chr/\u003e\u003cp\u003eThank you for your patience while we verify access. If you are in Reader mode please exit and \u003ca href=\"https://myaccount.nytimes.com/auth/login?response_type=cookie\u0026amp;client_id=vi\u0026amp;redirect_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F12%2F10%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Fsyria-civil-war-rebels-timeline-assad.html\u0026amp;asset=opttrunc\"\u003elog into\u003c/a\u003e your Times account, or \u003ca href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/subscription?campaignId=89WYR\u0026amp;redirect_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F12%2F10%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Fsyria-civil-war-rebels-timeline-assad.html\"\u003esubscribe\u003c/a\u003e for all of The Times.\u003c/p\u003e\u003chr/\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv data-testid=\"optimistic-truncator